<wi type="G" value="1537,5,">de</wi>
<wi type="G" value="846,6,">ellos</wi>
<rf><citebib id="WEB"/>
  dice `cuya genealogía no se cuenta de ellos,´
<citebib id="RVG2012"/> dice `cuya genealogía no es contada de ellos.´
  Según <citebib id="Thayer-BLB"/> la palabra griega `γενεαλογούμενος´
  se traduce como el acto del genealogista, recontar el origen y linaje
  de una familia, trazar ancestros.
</rf></rb>
<t xml:lang="es">
<wi type="G" value="1183,7,">recibió los diezmos</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,8,"/><wi type="G" value="11,9,">de Abraham</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="2532,10,">y</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2127,15,">bendijo</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,11,">al que</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2192,12,">tiene</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,13,"><wi type="G" value="1860,14,">las promesas</wi></wi>.</t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-7">
  But without any dispute the less
  is blessed by the better.
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="1161,2,">Y</wi>
<wi type="G" value="5565,1,">sin</wi>
<wi type="G" value="485,4,">contradicción</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3956,3,">alguna</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,5,"/><wi type="G" value="1640,6,">el menor</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2127,10,">es bendecido</wi>
<wi type="G" value="5259,7,">por</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,8,"/><wi type="G" value="2909,9,">el mejor</wi>.</t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-8">
Here people who die receive tithes, but there
one receives tithes of whom it is testified that he lives.
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="2532,1,">Y</wi>
 <wi type="G" value="5602,2,">aquí</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="3303,3,">de hecho</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="444,6,">los hombres</wi>
<wi type="G" value="599,5,">mortales</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2983,7,">reciben</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1181,4,">los diezmos</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="1161,9,">pero</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1563,8,">allá</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3140,10,">de quien se testifica</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3754,11,">que</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2198,12,">vive</wi>.</t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-9">
So to say,
through Abraham even Levi, who receives tithes, has paid tithes,
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="2532,1,">Y</wi>
<wi type="G" value="5613,2,">como</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2031,3,"/><wi type="G" value="2036,4,">digo</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1223,5,">mediante</wi>
<wi type="G" value="11,6,">Abraham</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2532,7,">incluso</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3017,8,">Levi</wi>, que
<wi type="G" value="2983,11,">recibe</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,9,"/><wi type="G" value="1181,10,">diezmos</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="1183,12,">ha pagado diezmos</wi>, </t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-10">
for he
was yet in the body of his father when Melchizedek met him.
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="1063,2,">pues</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2089,1,">aún</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2258,8,">él estaba</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1722,3,">en</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,4,"><wi type="G" value="3751,5,">el lomo</wi></wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,6,"><wi type="G" value="3962,7,">de su padre</wi></wi>
<wi type="G" value="3753,9,">cuando</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,12,"/><wi type="G" value="3198,13,">Melquisedec</wi>
<wi type="G" value="846,11,">lo</wi>
<wi type="G" value="4876,10,">conoció</wi></t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-11">
Now if
there was perfection through the Levitical priesthood (for under it the
people have received the law), what further need was there for another priest
to arise after the order of Melchizedek, and not be called after the order of
Aaron?
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="3303,2,">De hecho</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3767,3,">entonces</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1487,1,">si</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2258,9,">hubiera</wi>
<wi type="G" value="5050,4,">perfección</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1223,5,">mediante</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2420,8,">el sacerdocio</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,6,"/><wi type="G" value="3020,7,">Levítico</wi>
(<wi type="G" value="1063,12,">pues</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1909,13,">bajo</wi>
<wi type="G" value="846,14,">este</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,10,"><wi type="G" value="2992,11,">la gente</wi></wi>
<wi type="G" value="3549,15,">recibió la ley</wi>),
¿<wi type="G" value="5101,16,">qué</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2089,17,">más</wi>
<wi type="G" value="5532,18,">necesidad</wi> había de
<wi type="G" value="2087,23,">otro</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2409,25,">sacerdote</wi>
<wi type="G" value="450,24,">que se levantara</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2596,19,">del</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,20,"><wi type="G" value="5010,21,">orden</wi></wi>
<wi type="G" value="3198,22,">de Melquisedec</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="2532,26,">y</wi> que
<wi type="G" value="3756,27,">no</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3004,32,">fuera llamado</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2596,28,">del</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,29,"><wi type="G" value="5010,30,">orden</wi></wi>
<wi type="G" value="2,31,">de Aaron</wi>?
</t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-12">
For the priesthood being changed, there is of necessity a change
made also in the law.
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="1063,2,">Pues</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3346,1,">al cambiar</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,3,"><wi type="G" value="2420,4,">el sacerdocio</wi></wi>,
<wi type="G" value="2532,7,">también</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1096,10,">se crea</wi>
<wi type="G" value="318,6,">la necesidad</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1537,5,">de</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3331,9,">cambiar</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3551,8,">la ley</wi>.</t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-13">
For he of whom these things are said belongs to
another tribe, from which no one has officiated at the altar.
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="1063,3,">Pues</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1909,1,">de</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3739,2,">quien</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3004,4,">se dicen</wi>
<wi type="G" value="5023,5,">estas cosas</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3348,8,">pertenece a</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2087,7,">otra</wi>
<wi type="G" value="5443,6,">tribu</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="575,9,">de</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3739,10,">la cual</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3762,11,">nadie</wi>
<wi type="G" value="4337,12,">ha oficiado en</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,13,"><wi type="G" value="2379,14,">el altar</wi></wi>.
</t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-14">
For it is
evident that our Lord has sprung out of Judah, about which tribe Moses spoke
nothing concerning priesthood.
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="1063,2,">Pues</wi> es
<wi type="G" value="4271,1,">notorio</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3754,3,">que</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2257,9,">nuestro</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,7,"><wi type="G" value="2962,8,">Señor</wi></wi>
<wi type="G" value="393,6,">ha salido</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1537,4,">de</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2448,5,">Judá</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="5443,12,">tribu</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1519,10,">de</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3739,11,">la cual</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3475,16,">Moisés</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3762,13,">nada</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2980,17,">habló</wi>
<wi type="G" value="4012,14,">respecto</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2420,15,">al sacerdocio</wi>.</t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-15">
This is yet more abundantly evident, if
after the likeness of Melchizedek there arises another priest,
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="2532,1,">Y</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2076,5,">es</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2089,3,">aún</wi>
<wi type="G" value="4054,2,">más</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2612,4,">evidente</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="1487,6,">en que</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2596,7,">a</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,8,"><wi type="G" value="3665,9,">similitud</wi></wi>
<wi type="G" value="3198,10,">de Melquisedec</wi>
<wi type="G" value="450,11,">se levantó</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2087,13,">otro</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2409,12,">sacerdote</wi>,</t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-16">
who has
been made, not after the law of a fleshly commandment, but after the power of
an endless life:
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="3739,1,">quien</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1096,7,">fue constituido</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="3756,2,">no</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2596,3,">tras</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3551,4,">la ley</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1785,5,">de un mandato</wi>
<wi type="G" value="4559,6,">carnal</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="235,8,">sino</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2596,9,">tras</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1411,10,">el poder</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2222,11,">de la vida</wi>
<wi type="G" value="179,12,">inmortal</wi>:</t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-17">
for it is testified,
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="1063,2,">pues</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3140,1,">se testificó</wi><wi type="G" value="3754,3,"/>,</t>

<cl/><fp>
«You are a priest forever,
<t xml:lang="es">«<wi type="G" value="4771,4,">Tu</wi> eres
<wi type="G" value="2409,5,">sacerdote</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1519,6,">por</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,7,"><wi type="G" value="165,8,">siempre</wi></wi>,</t>
<cl/>
According to the order of Melchizedek.»
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="2596,9,">de acuerdo</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,10,"><wi type="G" value="5010,11,">al orden</wi></wi>
<wi type="G" value="3198,12,">de Melquisedec</wi>.»</t>
</fp>


</sv></cm><cm>

<sv id="Hebreos-7-18">
For there is an annulling of a foregoing commandment because of its
weakness and uselessness
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="1063,3,">Pues</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3303,2,">en verdad</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1096,4,">hay</wi>
<wi type="G" value="115,1,">una anulación</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1785,6,">del mandamiento</wi>
<wi type="G" value="4254,5,">existente</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1223,7,">por</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,8,"/><wi type="G" value="846,9,">su</wi>
<wi type="G" value="772,10,">débilidad</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2532,11,">e</wi>
<wi type="G" value="512,12,">inutilidad</wi></t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-19">
(for the law made nothing perfect), and a
bringing in thereupon of a better hope, through which we draw near to God.
<t xml:lang="es">(<wi type="G" value="1063,2,">pues</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,4,"><wi type="G" value="3551,5,">la ley</wi></wi>
<wi type="G" value="3762,1,">nada</wi>
<wi type="G" value="5048,3,">perfeccionó</wi>),
<wi type="G" value="1161,7,">pero</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1898,6,">la introducción</wi> de
<wi type="G" value="1680,9,">una esperanza</wi>
<wi type="G" value="2909,8,">mejor</wi>,
<wi type="G" value="1223,10,">por</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3739,11,">la que</wi>
<wi type="G" value="1448,12,">nos acercamos</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3588,13,"><wi type="G" value="2316,14,">a Dios</wi></wi>.</t>
</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-20">
Inasmuch as he was not made priest without the taking of an oath
<t xml:lang="es"><wi type="G" value="2532,1,"/><wi type="G" value="2596,2,">Por</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3745,3,">cuanto</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3756,4,">no</wi> </t>
<rb xml:lang="es"><rf>Para facilitar la lectura
<citebib id="WEB"/> and <citebib id="KJV2003"/> agregan
`fue hecho sacerdote.´</rf></rb>
<t xml:lang="es">
fue <wi type="G" value="5565,5,">sin</wi>
<wi type="G" value="3728,6,">un juramento</wi></t>

</sv>
<sv id="Hebreos-7-21">
(for they indeed have been made priests without an oath), but he with
an oath by him that says of him,
<t xml:lang="es">(<wi type="G" value="3588,1,"/><wi type="G" value="1063,3,">pues</wi>
